{'text': "### 1. Hourly Monitor Trigger

This `Cron` node will trigger the workflow automatically every **hour**.

**To change the schedule:** Adjust the 'Mode' or set specific 'Hour' and 'Minute' values to match how often you want to check the website (e.g., every 4 hours, daily).", 'position': 'right'}

{'text': "### 4. If Items Found (Conditional Check)

This `If` node checks if the 'Extract Job/Product Info' node actually found any items. If it did, the workflow continues down the 'True' path to send a notification.

**No configuration needed**; it checks if the array of extracted items is not empty.", 'position': 'right'}

parameters.function:
let summary = "";

if (items.length > 0) {
  summary = `**Found ${items.length} new/updated items!**\n\n`;
  for (const item of items) {
    // Assuming you extracted 'JobTitle' and 'JobLink' from HTML Extract
    const title = item.json.JobTitle || item.json.ProductName || 'N/A';
    const link = item.json.JobLink || 'No link';
    const otherInfo = item.json.StockStatus ? ` (Status: ${item.json.StockStatus})` : '';
    summary += `* **${title}**${otherInfo}\n  Link: ${link}\n\n`;
  }
} else {
  summary = "No new items found during this check.";
}

return [{ json: { notificationMessage: summary } }];
